# Synaptik Core (Python)

<p align="center">
  <a href="https://pypi.org/project/synaptik-core-beta/"><img src="https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/synaptik-core-beta.svg" alt="PyPI version"></a>
</p>

Python bindings for Synaptik Core — local-first cognitive substrate with durable memory, contract-governed safety controls, and audit trails for AI systems.

## Install

```bash
pip install synaptik-core-beta
```

## Quick Start

```python
import synaptik_core as sc

cmd = sc.PyCommands()

# Memory operations
mid = cmd.remember("chat", "hello world")
print(cmd.recall(mid))                  # -> {'id': ..., 'content': 'hello world', 'source': 'hot'}
print(cmd.recall(mid, prefer="archive")) # Prefer specific tier
print(cmd.recall_prefer(mid))            # -> 'hello world' (just content)

# Recent memories
recent_ids = cmd.recent("chat", n=10)    # Last 10 memory IDs

# Stats
stats = cmd.stats()                      # Workspace-wide stats
stats = cmd.stats(lobe="chat")          # Per-lobe stats

# Ethics & governance
report = cmd.precheck_text("message content", purpose="chat_response")
# -> {'decision': 'allow', 'reason': ..., 'risk': 'low', ...}

result = cmd.govern_text("chat.reply", "hello")
# -> {'status': 'ok', 'text': 'hello', 'violation_label': None}
```

## Branching and Consolidation (FF‑only)

High-level helpers move seeding, normalization, and provenance into the core.

```python
import synaptik_core as sc
cmd = sc.PyCommands()

# Sprout a dendrite; base resolution:
# - base=None,lobe=None: start from head('cortex') if present, else seed from 'chat'
# - base provided: interpreted as an existing path name (if it exists), otherwise as a CID
base_cid = cmd.sprout_dendrite(path="feature-x", base=None, lobe=None)

# Encode an engram (Ethos-gated) with optional meta
cid = cmd.encode_engram(path="feature-x", content="...", meta={"file": "lru.rs"})

# Systems consolidation to cortex (FF-only; errors if not FF)
head = cmd.systems_consolidate(src_path="feature-x", dst_path="cortex")

# Potentiate a synapse (accepts memory IDs, hashes, or node filenames)
weight = cmd.potentiate_synapse(cid)
print("synaptic weight:", weight)

# Inspect history and recall
trace = cmd.trace_path("feature-x", limit=10)
snap = cmd.recall(head)           # dict or None
content = cmd.recall_prefer(head) # str or None
```

Notes:
- Paths normalize to lowercase; “feature-x” and “feature_x” are equivalent.
- Consolidation is fast‑forward only; binds are not yet supported.
- Prefer `sprout_dendrite()/encode_engram()/systems_consolidate()/potentiate_synapse()`; legacy `begin_branch/extend_path` remain for compatibility.

## Object Storage (PonStore)

Content-addressed binary storage with versioning:

```python
# Create a Pon (object store)
cmd.pons_create("models")

# Store binary data
cmd.pons_put_object("models", key="embed-v1", data=model_bytes, 
                    media_type="application/octet-stream")

# Retrieve latest version
ref = cmd.pons_get_latest_ref("models", "embed-v1")
data = cmd.pons_get_latest_bytes("models", "embed-v1")

# List all keys
keys = cmd.pons_list_latest("models")
```

## Workspace Configuration

```python
# Get workspace configuration
config = cmd.get_config()
# -> {'cache_path': '.cogniv/cache.db', 'sandbox_mode': True, 'hot_threshold': 86400, ...}

# Get workspace root path
root = cmd.get_root()  # -> '.cogniv'
```

